reset().Description: Removes the Element and Window references from this interaction. This is usually necessary when a prior action (for example a click) introduces a navigation that invalidates the ElementReference and WindowReference pointers.

withNoTimeout().Description: Disables all Timeouts on this WebInteraction. Javascript evaluation is performed asynchronously on the WebKit/Chromium thread. By default we wait a short while for the result to be delivered back to the test.

get().Description: Returns the result of a prior call to perform or check.

withTimeout(long, java.util.concurrent.T.Description: Sets a specific timeout for this WebInteraction.

forceJavascriptEnabled().Description: Performs a force enable of Javascript on a WebView. All WebView interactions are done via Javascript - therefore the WebView we are working on must support Javascript evaluation. Enabling Javascript may cause the WebView under test to be reloaded. This is necessary to ensure the test infrastructure javascript bridges are loaded by the WebView.

ClassDesc: Analogous to a ViewInteraction or a DataInteraction, a WebInteraction exposes a fluent API to the underlying WebView.
